OL,7,FFinding that Mr Gilbert's fitness to
OL,8,Fpractise was impaired because of
OL,9,Fmisconduct, tribunal chairman Andrew
OL,10,FMcLoughlin said: "The Tribunal
OL,11,Fconcluded that Mr Gilbert had
OL,12,Fdemonstrated a significant degree of
OL,13,Finsight and had taken a number of
OL,14,Fsteps to remediate his failings.
OL,16,F"However, Mr Gilbert's insight was not
OL,17,Ffully developed into the full extent
OL,18,Fof his behaviour as found proved by
OL,19,Fthe Tribunal.
